The paper deals with computing the persistent homology of simplicial complexes, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG) and topological data analysis (cs.DS). The use of strong collapses to simplify the complexes is a technique in algebraic topology (cs.DM), and the approach's efficiency and memory usage are relevant to computer science (cs.SI) and machine learning (cs.LG).
